verse:
5 “Sit in silence, go into darkness, queen city of the Babylonians;
no more will you be called queen of kingdoms. 6 I was angry with my people and desecrated my inheritance;
I gave them into your hand, and you showed them no mercy.
Even on the aged you laid a very heavy yoke. 7 You said, ‘I am forever— the eternal queen!’
But you did not consider these things or reflect on what might happen.
